ABUJA – Chief Audu Ogbeh, Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, has joined other well-meaning Nigerians to congratulate President Muhammadu Buhari, on his victory at the just concluded Presidential and National Assembly elections. A statement on Friday by Mr. Mohammed Nakorji, Director of Information in the Federal Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, quoted Ogbeh as saying that Buhari’s victory at the poll did not come as a surprise especially with the giant strides recorded in the nation’s agricultural sector, particularly the rice revolution among others. He assured the nation that with the re-election of Mr. President for a second term the Agriculture Ministry which he oversees would consolidate on its achievements and move the nation’s agricultural sector to the next level.